
design mechanism to transfer data.

there are 2 ways to transfer data.

1. active; the data is directly transfered from one space to another
    network file transfer
    local file copy
2. passive; the file is linked or otherwise connected to the user
    sshfs; nfs;

one parameter for the transfer indicates read-only or modify-allowed
this will impact the possible ways to make the move the data.

read only tranfers need to ensure there is no way the original can be modified.
this can be done using copy with no copy-back; or a link which does not allow
any modifications.

write-allowed tranfers need to ensure that changes are propigated promptly and that
no other jobs can modify the data outside the current job unless parallelism is
enabled.

parallel data can be enabled but all jobs then need to manage locks or some other
feature to ensure data integrity.
